全球股市结束“黑色一周”，世卫将疫情风险调至最高级。
Global stock markets ended a "black week," with WHO shifting the risk of the epidemic to the top.
金焱。
Yan, Jin.
财经杂志                      。
Financial magazine.
财经杂志。
Financial magazine.
《财经》杂志官方微信。
An official letter from Caijing magazine.
《财经》杂志由中国证券市场研究中心主办，1998年创刊，秉承“独立、独家、独到”的新闻理念，以权威性、公正性、专业性报道见长，是政经学界决策者、研究者、管理者的必读刊物。
"Caijing" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was founded in 1998, upholding the news concept of "independence, exclusivity and originality," and providing authoritative, impartial and professional reports.
。
.
美联储2月28日市场交易结束时进行了救援，发出强烈信号会尽快降息。
The Fed bailed out the markets on Feb. 28, sending a strong signal that it would cut rates as quickly as possible.
这会使金融市场至少平静几天。
That would calm financial markets for at least a few days.
市场随后反弹还是继续下滑，取决于美国及全球新冠肺炎疫情的走势文 |《财经》特派记者金焱发自华盛顿 编辑 | 苏琦世界卫生组织总干事谭德塞2月28日在日内瓦宣布，鉴于最近几天在中国境外受新型冠状病毒疫情影响的国家和病例数量持续增加，决定将新冠肺炎疫情级别由此前的“高”上调至“非常高”的水平。
China's new coronavirus outbreak has been raised to very high levels in recent days as the number of countries and cases affected by the new-type coronavirus outside China continues to rise, officials said Tuesday.
这是世卫组织风险评估的最高级。
This is the highest level of WHO risk assessment.
当疫情最初的影响主要控制在中国境内时，美国金融市场反应并不强烈。
When the initial impact of the outbreak was largely contained within China, the response of the United States financial markets was not strong.
当中国疫情控制效果得以显现，韩国、日本、意大利、伊朗等国的确诊病例却开始大幅增长。
While the effects of China's epidemic have been demonstrated, the number of confirmed cases in South Korea, Japan, Italy, and Iran has risen sharply.
这让美欧金融市场终于感受到疫情冲击风险，随即出现持续一周的断崖式全线下跌。
That left financial markets in the US and Europe at last feeling the risk of an epidemic, followed by a week-long fall across the cliff.
韩国疾病管理本部2月28日下午宣布，新增新冠病毒确诊病例571例，打破27日的505例，再创单日新高纪录。
A record 571 new cases were confirmed, breaking the 27-day record of 505 cases, the ministry said on the afternoon of Feb. 28.
伊朗是海湾地区唯一报告有新冠病毒感染死亡的国家，也是中国以外死亡病例最多的国家。
Iran is the only country in the Gulf region to report a new crown virus infection-related death and the largest number of deaths outside China.
病毒扩散的恐慌情绪疫情严重干扰国际旅行和供应链，加剧了人们对美国和欧元区经济可能会走向衰退的担忧。
Panic over the spread of the virus has severely disrupted international travel and supply chains, heightening fears that the US and eurozone economies could head into recession.
美东时间2月28日（周五），投资者担心疫情将打击全球经济，连续大跌之后，全球股市仍跌势不止。
Stock markets around the world continued to tumble on Friday, Feb. 28, amid fears that the global economy would be hit by the outbreak.
欧洲股市再度重挫，截至收盘，欧洲斯托克50指数跌3.62%，德国DAX指数跌3.86%、英国富时100指数跌3.18%，法国CAC40指数跌3.38%。
European stocks tumbled again, with Europe's Stoke 50 down 3.62 per cent, Germany's DAX down 3.86 per cent, the FTSE 100 down 3.18 per cent and the French CAC40 down 3.38 per cent.
美股集体低开，道指盘中跌逾1000点。
U.S. stocks closed lower, down more than 1,000 points in the Dow Jones trading.
截止收盘，美股三大股指涨跌不一，道指跌1.38%，纳指微涨0.01%，标普500指数跌0.83%。
By the end of trading, the three main U.S. stock indexes were mixed, with the Dow down 1.38%, the NDI up 0.01%, and the S & P 500 down 0.83%.
2月24日至2月28日这一周，美股创2008年金融危机以来的最差一周表现，美三大股指均累计下跌超10%。
During the week of Feb. 24 to Feb. 28, U.S. stocks posted their worst week since the 2008 financial crisis, with all three U.S. stock indexes down more than 10%.
欧洲斯托克50指数跌逾12%，伦敦股市《金融时报》100种股票平均价格指数跌超11%，法国巴黎股市CAC40指数累跌近12%，德国法兰克福股市DAX指数跌逾12%。
Europe's Stoke 50 index fell more than 12 per cent, London's Financial Times average of 100 stocks fell below 11 per cent, the French stock market CAC40 fell nearly 12 per cent and the German Frankfurt DAX index fell more than 12 per cent.
美股尾盘三大股指强势反弹，道指在2月28日从低点反弹逾700点，纳指收复超3%的跌幅。
The three main indexes rebounded strongly in the late US session as the Dow rallied more than 700 points from their lows on February 28, recovering more than 3 per cent of the decline.
对于市场的表现，评级机构穆迪公司（Moody's）旗下穆迪分析（Moody’s Analytics ）首席经济学家马克·赞迪（Mark Zandi）对《财经》记者指出，美联储在周五市场交易结束时进行了救援，并发出强烈信号会尽快降息。
Mark Zandi, chief economist at Moody's Analytics, the rating agency Moody's, told Caijing that the Fed bailed out Friday at the end of trading and sent a strong signal that it would cut rates as soon as possible.
这会使金融市场平静至少几天。
That would calm financial markets for at least a few days.
市场随后反弹还是继续下滑，这要取决于新冠肺炎疫情的走势。
The market then rebounded or continued to decline, depending on the trend of the new crown pneumonia epidemic.
金融市场如此关键时刻，美联储主席鲍威尔2月28日发表声明：“美国经济基本面强劲。
At this critical juncture in financial markets, Federal Reserve Chairman Colin Powell issued a statement on February 28: "The fundamentals of the US economy are strong.
同时，新冠肺炎疫情对经济活动造成的风险不断变化。
At the same time, the risks posed to economic activity by the new crown pneumonia epidemic are constantly changing.
美联储正密切关注事态进展及其对经济前景的影响。
The Fed is closely watching developments and their implications for the economic outlook.
我们会利用货币政策工具、在必要的时机为经济提供支撑。
We will use the tools of monetary policy to prop up the economy when necessary.
”谭德塞表示，几个国家出现了相互关联的疫情发展，但多数病例仍然可追踪到密切者，且并未发现病毒在社区自由传播的证据。
Mr Tanner said there were interrelated outbreaks in several countries, but most cases were still traceable to close people and no evidence of the virus spreading freely in the community.
他强调，控制疫情的关键是阻断病毒传播链条。
He stressed that the key to controlling the epidemic is to stop the virus transmission chain.
如果采取强有力的行动尽早发现病例、对病人进行隔离和护理、追踪密切接触者，“我们仍有机会控制这种病毒”。
If strong action is taken to identify cases early, isolate and care for patients, and track close contacts, "we still have a chance to control the virus."
美联储能否救市？美股2月28日大幅低开，早间道指一度狂泻逾1000点，延续了本周前期的暴跌趋势。
U.S. stocks opened sharply lower on Feb. 28, continuing a steep decline earlier this week as the Dow tumbled more than 1,000 points in the early morning session.
本周美股创2008年金融危机以来的最差一周表现，标普500指数累计下跌11.5%，纳指下跌10.5%，道指下跌12.4%。
This week, U.S. stocks posted their worst week since the 2008 financial crisis, with the S & P 500 down 11.5%, the index down 10.5% and the Dow down 12.4%.
2月份，标普500指数下跌8.4%，道指跌10%，纳指跌6.4%。
In February, the S & P 500 fell 8.4%, with the Dow down 10% and the NV down 6.4%.
2月24日至28日这一周美股连续重挫，三大基准股指周四收盘时均已跌入回调区。
The week from Feb. 24 to Feb. 28 saw U.S. stocks tumble, with all three benchmark indexes closing Thursday in the correction zone.
标普500指数仅用6个交易日就回调，是史上用时最短的回调过程。
The S & P 500 is the shortest callback in history, with only six trading days to go.
所谓回调，其定义为从近期峰值下跌至少10%、但不超过20%。
A callback is defined as a drop of at least 10 per cent, but not more than 20 per cent, from its recent peak.
对于标普500指数和纳斯达克指数而言，二者均在周四录得2011年8月18日以来的最大日百分比跌幅，道琼斯指数则录得自2018年2月5日以来的最大百分比跌幅。
For both the S & P 500 and the Nasdaq, both recorded their biggest daily percentage declines since August 18, 2011, while the Dow fell by the largest percentage point since February 5, 2018.
市场的恐慌情绪以及疫情导致需求下降的利空不只反映在价格上，也反映在恐慌性抛售上。
The panic in the markets and the slump in demand caused by the outbreak are reflected not only in prices but also in panic selling.
多伦多交易所母公司TMX集团周五在社交媒体上宣布，受到订单系统故障的影响，多伦多交易所、多伦多创业板市场以及Alpha交易系统已经停止交易。
The Toronto Stock Exchange's parent company, TMX Group, announced on social media Friday that trading had stopped on the Toronto Stock Exchange, Toronto GEM and Alpha trading systems because of a breakdown in the order system.
受多伦多证交所停市影响，加拿大唯一的金融衍生品与期货交易所——蒙特利尔证交所也在同一日宣布停市。
The Montreal Stock Exchange, Canada's only derivatives and futures exchange, also closed on the same day, following the Toronto Stock Exchange's closure.
多伦多证券交易所所有者TMX集团(TMX Group)解释称，由于“技术问题”，该交易所已暂停交易。
TMX Group, the owner of the Toronto Stock Exchange, explained that the exchange had suspended trading because of "technical problems."
有市场分析人士则认为，可能由于对冠状病毒的担忧，从而引发了恐慌性抛盘，据悉，在暂停交易前，多伦多证券交易所的交易量已经超过了30天的平均水平。
Some market analysts believe the fear of a coronavirus could trigger a panic selling, with trading on the Toronto Stock Exchange already above the 30-day average before the suspension.
FactSet的数据显示，本周四有超过2.32亿股股票易手，超过30天均值的2.311亿股。
More than 232 million shares changed hands Thursday, exceeding the 30-day average of 231.1 million, according to FactSet.
国际货币基金组织前首席经济学家、哈佛大学经济及公共政策教授肯尼思·罗戈夫在接受采访时表示，全球陷入严重衰退的可能性高于金融危机以来的任何时候。
In an interview, Kenneth Rogoff, a former chief economist of the International Monetary Fund and a professor of economics and public policy at Harvard University, said the likelihood of a severe global recession was higher than at any time since the financial crisis.
随着投资者的担心不断放大，美联储救市的呼声也越来越高。
As investor fears mount, calls for a Fed bail-out mount.
美联储官员近期的声明暗示他们还不相信有必要采取行动，不过，芝加哥商业交易所集团的数据显示，美国时间周四中午，交易员用来押注美联储政策走向的联邦基金利率期货显示，投资者认为美联储在3月17日至18日议息会议上将关键政策利率下调0.25个百分点的几率为72%。
Recent statements by Fed officials suggest they don't yet believe it is necessary, but data from the Chicago Mercantile Exchange Group show that at noon on Thursday, traders bet on the direction of Fed policy, Federal Fund rate futures, which traders used to bet on Fed policy, showed a 72% chance that the Fed would cut key policy rates by 0.25 percentage points at its March 17-18 meeting.
而一周前该几率仅为9%。
That's up from 9% a week ago.
加之利率和通胀已处于低位，人们相信美联储可能需要采取积极措施削减借贷成本，以缓解这种新型冠状病毒的迅速蔓延对经济的冲击。
Combined with low interest rates and inflation, it is believed that the Fed may need to take aggressive measures to reduce borrowing costs in order to mitigate the economic impact of the new coronavirus.
最大的敌人是恐惧、谣言和污名化截至目前已有至少48个国家和地区报告了感染病例。
The worst enemy is fear, rumour and stigmatization. So far, at least 48 countries and territories have reported cases of infection.
联合国秘书长古特雷斯28日在纽约总部向新闻界发表谈话时评论说，这不是惊慌的时刻，而是进行准备——充分准备——的时刻。
This is not a time of panic, but a time to prepare - to be prepared - the Secretary-General of the United Nations, Carlos Guterres, said in a statement to the press yesterday at New York headquarters.
现在是所有国家政府加紧努力并尽一切可能遏制疫情的时候了，并且应当是在没有侮辱和尊重人权的情况下做到这一点。
The time has come for all Governments to intensify their efforts and do everything possible to contain the epidemic, and to do so without humiliation and with respect for human rights.
古特雷斯说：”我们知道可以遏制疫情，但是机会之窗正在缩小。
"We know we can contain it, but the window of opportunity is closing," said Guterres.
因此，我呼吁所有国家都承担起责任，展示团结和全面的全球支持。
I therefore call on all States to shoulder their responsibilities and demonstrate solidarity and comprehensive global support.
在这样做的同时，所有国家都应有信心，他们将得到联合国和世界卫生组织的支持。
In doing so, all countries should be confident that they will have the support of the United Nations and the World Health Organization.
“以意大利和伊朗为中心，欧洲和中东疫情持续升级。
"With Italy and Iran at the centre, the epidemic continues to escalate in Europe and the Middle East.
当地时间2月28日傍晚，意大利民防部门负责人博雷利在例行疫情通报中表示，截至当天17时（北京时间2月29日0时），意大利共计确诊新型冠状病毒肺炎病例888例，较前一天增加238例。
Italy confirmed 888 new cases of coronavirus pneumonia by 1700 hours (0000 hours Beijing time), 238 cases more than the previous day, the head of Italy's civil defence department, Aurelio Borelli, said on the evening of February 28, local time.
其中21人死亡，46人康复。
Of these, 21 died and 46 recovered.
博雷利指出，在现有确诊病例中，412人属于无症状或轻症状患者，64人接受重症监护治疗。
Of the existing confirmed cases, 412 were asymptomatic or mildly symptomatic and 64 were under intensive care, Borelli said.
另外，新增的4名死亡病例年龄都超过75岁。
In addition, four of the new deaths were over 75 years of age.
至此，意大利共有13个大区和1个自治省出现新冠肺炎疫情。
So far, Italy has 13 regions and one autonomous province of the New Crown Pneumonia outbreak.
伊朗是海湾地区唯一报告有新冠病毒感染死亡的国家，也是中国以外死亡病例最多的国家。
Iran is the only country in the Gulf region to report a new crown virus infection-related death and the largest number of deaths outside China.
目前该国确诊病例超过300例，感染者中也包括伊朗副总统和卫生部副部长。
There are now more than 300 confirmed cases in the country, including the Vice-President of Iran and the Deputy Minister of Health.
在其他海湾国家里，科威特、巴林、阿联酋和阿曼都有感染病例。
In other Gulf States, Kuwait, Bahrain, the United Arab Emirates and Oman have cases of infection.
由于疫情蔓延，德黑兰已经取消了23省的首府在周五的祈祷活动，包括德黑兰和什叶派圣城库姆和马什哈德。
Tehran has cancelled Friday prayers in 23 provincial capitals, including Tehran and the Shiite holy cities of Qom and Mashhad, as the outbreak spread.
曾在非典期间主持美方相关人士与中国疾病预防控制中心跨洋电话会议的、前德州大学达拉斯分校副校长冯达旋对《财经》记者说，病毒是最民主的，它对所有人都一视同仁。
'Viruses are the most democratic and treat everyone the same, 'Feng Daxuan, a former vice president of the University of Texas at Dallas, who chaired a trans-oceanic conference call with the CDC during SARS, told Caijing.
日本和中国2月28日周五决定在应对新冠病毒疫情方面展开双边合作。
Japan and China decided on Friday, Feb. 28, to cooperate bilaterally in the fight against the new crown virus.
为防止新冠病毒入侵，美国海军2月28日颁布新措施，命令所有在太平洋海域港口停靠过的军舰都必须在海上自我隔离14天。
The Navy on Feb. 28 ordered all ships calling at Pacific ports to isolate themselves at sea for up to 14 days in an effort to prevent a possible New Crown Virus invasion.
美国海军发言人詹姆斯·亚当斯（James Adams）中尉说：“出于谨慎起见，太平洋舰队正在执行一项新的防范措施，避免船员感染新冠病毒，并对前往高风险地区的船员进行监控。
US Navy spokesman Lieutenant James Adams said: "As a precaution, the Pacific Fleet is implementing a new precautionary measure to prevent Crew members from getting infected with the Crown virus and to monitor crews going to high-risk areas.
目前没有迹象显示有美国海军人员受到病毒感染。
There are no immediate indications that U. S. Navy personnel have been infected.
